- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the performance of linear probing, a common data structure used in computer science. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the independence required for hash functions, which is a topic related to information theory. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with the construction of hash functions, which involves discrete mathematics. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the time complexity of linear probing and minwise independence. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as hash functions are also used in cryptography and security.
